Oyarsa-Q comment:
This film takes you on a soaring psychedelic trip to another space and time, a very weird and wonderful place. Such a massive quantity of LSD was ingested by the people in the film (and behind the cameras too, no doubt) you will unavoidably get a most powerful contact high. Like no other documentary I've seen, it's full of sumptuous, dazzling visuals, a feast for the senses, a delight to behold. It's a wonder and a miracle that this other-wordly and essential historical story could be told at all. We are indeed blessed to have all this incredible footage.


